<div id="review_343269256" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/343269256" />
    <a title="brinley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8725179-brinley"><img alt="brinley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556813238p2/8725179.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/343269256?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="brinley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="brinley" href="/user/show/8725179-brinley">brinley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer343269256" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15797919349959261499">Not necessarily the best writing, but this was definitely a captivating story-line and deals with a lot of sensitive issues that I think most people feel uncomfortable with. Ultimately I took this as a meditation on challenging the things taught (through whatever authorities you are taught them through) that are acceptable, beautiful, or worth preserving. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

