<div id="review_248919953" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/248919953" />
    <a title="Kathryn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/295681-kathryn"><img alt="Kathryn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1220649653p2/295681.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/248919953?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathryn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathryn" href="/user/show/295681-kathryn">Kathryn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer248919953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer147569243282631440">Not even 2 chapters in and already we have covered so many hot button topics in Africa... AIDS research, cloning, skin bleaching, color based kaste systems, prison accomodations, smuggling... The author has me by the throat and she is NOT letting go.<br/><br/>She never did. This book makes me want to be mad at myself for being born white. Confusing and tender and awful and every roller coaster of emotion.<br/>So so good.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


