<div id="review_264089631" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/264089631" />
    <a title="Aiesha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/656900-aiesha"><img alt="Aiesha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1291565003p2/656900.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/264089631?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aiesha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aiesha" href="/user/show/656900-aiesha">Aiesha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer264089631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10166699591248841022">This book is not linear, which I like, because life doesn&apos;t flow from point A to B and neither do our thoughts. I loved the beautiful imagery, the characters, and how Boof explored, science, AIDS, race, self-hatred, colonialism and more. This book can be categorized as so many things: fantasy, Afro-futurism and more. It reminds me of Octavia Butler in how I can see some of what Boof talks about come to pass in our near future.</span>
  <span id="freeText10166699591248841022" style="display:none">This book is not linear, which I like, because life doesn't flow from point A to B and neither do our thoughts. I loved the beautiful imagery, the characters, and how Boof explored, science, AIDS, race, self-hatred, colonialism and more. This book can be categorized as so many things: fantasy, Afro-futurism and more. It reminds me of Octavia Butler in how I can see some of what Boof talks about come to pass in our near future.</span>
