<div id="review_3900800038" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3900800038" />
    <a title="Kristen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/755464-kristen"><img alt="Kristen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442482835p2/755464.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3900800038?book_show_action=true">Mar 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristen" href="/user/show/755464-kristen">Kristen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3900800038&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3900800038" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14322043704575055920">Stunning speculative fiction with great insight on African diversity and bitter racial themes so creativity played. Lyrical, engaging writing -- sexy and intelligent, tremendously creepy.<br/><br/>I had a problem with the ending...<br/><br/>_________<br/><br/> SPOILER ALERT!<br/>__________<br/><br/><br/>.<br/>.<br/>.<br/>.<br/>.<br/>.<br/>.<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>If she could start her own country, why couldn&apos;t she start her own movie studio?</span>
  <span id="freeText14322043704575055920" style="display:none">Stunning speculative fiction with great insight on African diversity and bitter racial themes so creativity played. Lyrical, engaging writing -- sexy and intelligent, tremendously creepy.<br /><br />I had a problem with the ending...<br /><br />_________<br /><br /> SPOILER ALERT!<br />__________<br /><br /><br />.<br />.<br />.<br />.<br />.<br />.<br />.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />If she could start her own country, why couldn't she start her own movie studio?</span>
